The paper deals with optimization problems in the context of agents with limited resources, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses multi-agent scenarios, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The problem of optimizing resource allocation and usage is also relevant to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses mixed integer linear programming (MILP) formulations, which is a common technique in optimization and machine learning (cs.LG).
